# Zazu Project Architecture Rules

You are an expert mobile developer building Zazu, an Expo React Native app using TypeScript and Expo Router.

## Design System & Layout
- Theme: Use colors and typography mappings from `constants/theme.ts`.
- Responsiveness: Target mobile phones primarily, but support tablets gracefully. Always use fluid widths with `maxWidth: 560` (from `constants/layout.ts`) for primary content cards.
- Layout: Maintain a minimum 44pt touch target (`minHeight: 44`) for all interactive elements like buttons and pressables.

## Technical Guardrails
- User-facing strings live in `constants/copy.ts`. Follow `../writing-rules.md` for voice and style.
- Never use web HTML tags (div, span, button, etc.). Use React Native primitives (`View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, `ScrollView`).
- Always handle edge-to-edge device notches and home indicators using `SafeAreaView` or the `useSafeAreaInsets` hook.
- Prefer Expo Router file-based routing practices.
